### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

forms

### Description

`ValidatorFn` and ` AsyncValidatorFn` accept a parameter of type `AbstractControl`.
If an app is generated with `--strict` flag or `"strict": true` is manually added to tsconfig compilerOptions, following code reports an error:

```ts
// TS2322: Type '(control: FormControl<string>) => ValidationErrors | null' is not assignable to type 'ValidatorFn'.
//   Types of parameters 'control' and 'control' are incompatible.
//     Type 'AbstractControl<any, any>' is missing the following properties from type 'FormControl<string>': defaultValue, registerOnChange, registerOnDisabledChange
const userNameValidator: ValidatorFn = (
    control: FormControl<string>
): ValidationErrors | null => null;

const ctrl: FormControl<string> = new FormControl<string>('', {
    nonNullable: true,
    validators: [userNameValidator],
});
```

This would be especially useful when adding a validator to the whole form:

```ts
interface User {
    name: string;
    age: number;
}

type UserFormType = {
    [K in keyof User]: FormControl<User[K]>;
};

const formValidator: ValidatorFn = (
    form: FormGroup<UserFormType>
): ValidationErrors | null => null;

const userNameValidator: ValidatorFn = (
    control: FormControl<string>
): ValidationErrors | null => null;

const ageValidator: ValidatorFn = (form: FormControl<number>): ValidationErrors | null =>
    null;

const form: FormGroup<UserFormType> = new FormGroup<UserFormType>(
    {
        name: new FormControl<string>('', {
            nonNullable: true,
            validators: [userNameValidator],
        }),
        age: new FormControl<number>(0, {
            nonNullable: true,
            validators: [ageValidator],
        }),
    },
    {
        validators: [formValidator],
    }
);
```

### Proposed solution

`ValidatorFn` and `AsyncValidatorFn` should be typed to accept the type of the control they'll get, e.g.

```ts
interface ValidatorFn<T extends AbstractControl = AbstractControl> {
  (control: T): ValidationErrors | null;
}

interface AsyncValidatorFn<T extends AbstractControl = AbstractControl> {
  (control: T): Observable<ValidationErrors | null> | Promise<ValidationErrors | null>;
}
```

### Alternatives considered

Casting custom validator functions to `ValidatorFn`:
```ts
const formValidator: ValidatorFn = ((
    form: FormGroup<UserFormType>
): ValidationErrors | null => null) as ValidatorFn;
```

Accepting `AbstractControl` and casting it internally:
```ts
const formValidator2: ValidatorFn = (
    _form: AbstractControl
): ValidationErrors | null => {
    const form: FormGroup<UserFormType> = _form as FormGroup<UserFormType>;
    // ...
    return null!
};
```
